article.headline: Florida State 69, Montana 56
article.story:
TALLAHASSEE, Fla. (AP) -- Ganiyat Adeduntan scored 13 points and
grabbed six rebounds Sunday to lead Florida State to a 69-56
victory over Montana in the championship game of the Seminole
Classic.

The Lady Griz (3-1) trailed 11-7, with 14:20 to play in the
first half after a 3-pointer by Katie Edwards, but Florida State
(4-1) went on a 17-2 run over the next 4:46 to take a 28-9 lead.

FSU led 36-15 with 5:10 to play, but Montana shut the Seminoles
out the rest of the half and pulled within 36-23 at the break after
Dana Conway scored the final five points of the half. Conway led
Montana with a career high 18 points. She also grabbed six
rebounds.

Florida State built as much as a 48-29 lead on a basket by
LaQuinta Neely with 12:40 remaining. Montana rallied to within
56-47 on two free throws by Conway with 5:56 remaining.

Senior Jody McLeod pulled Montana within 60-53 on an inside
basket with 3:26 remaining, but the Seminoles' Nikki Anthony hit a
jumper to make it 62-53, ending UM's comeback.

Holly Johnson had 11 points for FSU while Anthony and Britany
Miller scored 10 each.

Johanna Closson added 12 points and Katie Edwards 11. Edwards
was named to the all tournament team after averaging 17.5 points in
UM's two games.
